        <strong>Suspensions</strong> <br>
        <br>
        A player receiving three yellow cards consecutively shall be banned from 
        playing in the next game. On receipt of another three yellow cards, another 
        one game ban takes place. A player reaching nine yellow cards will receive 
        an automatic two-match ban. A player receiving 12 yellow cards will receive 
        an automatic two-match ban, and will be asked to meet the League Committee. 
        A red card results in a one game ban. However, if the red card is received 
        for violent conduct with intent to hurt then the ban shall be a minimum 
        of two games. Repeat offenders will be banned from playing in the League. 
        The League Committee would report the incident to the police if necessary. 
        The League Committee can only take decisions of this kind after consultation 
        of the referee and both Team Managers involved. <br>
        Suspensions can be served in both tournament matches and cup matches. 
        <br>
        Team Managers shall state clearly in the Match Report the name of their 
        team&#8217;s players, and their opponents&#8217; players, who have received 
        cards.</p>
